# Writing Functions

## Signature

- **Verb in name**: `getPatient`, `formatDate`, `validatePhone`.
- **Explicit return type** on public functions.
- **Parameter order**: client/context → ids → payload.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
async function getPatientById(supabase: SupabaseClient, id: string): Promise<Patient | null> {
  const { data } = await supabase.from('patients').select('*').eq('id', id).maybeSingle();
  return data;
}

function formatBirthDate(date: Date): string {
  return date.toLocaleDateString('pt-BR');
}

// ❌ BAD
async function patient(supabase: SupabaseClient, id: string) {  // no verb, no return type
```

## Early Return

- Exit early on invalid input or edge cases; avoid deep nesting.
- Put the "happy path" at the top or after guards.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
function processPatient(patient: Patient | null): string {
  if (!patient) return '';
  if (!patient.name?.trim()) return '';
  return patient.name;
}

// ❌ BAD
function processPatient(patient: Patient | null): string {
  if (patient) {
    if (patient.name?.trim()) {
      return patient.name;
    }
  }
  return '';
}
```

## Purity

- **Pure functions** when possible: same inputs → same output; no I/O, no mutation.
- Separate I/O (fetch, Supabase, localStorage) from logic.
- Do **not mutate** arguments; return new values.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD – pure
function fullName(first: string, last: string): string {
  return `${first} ${last}`.trim();
}

// ✅ GOOD – I/O isolated
async function fetchPatient(supabase: SupabaseClient, id: string): Promise<Patient> {
  const { data, error } = await supabase.from('patients').select('*').eq('id', id).single();
  if (error) throw new Error(error.message);
  return data;
}
```

## Errors

- **Validate inputs** at the start; throw `ValidationError` for bad input.
- Do **not swallow** errors; log and rethrow or return a typed result.
- One responsibility; if validation fails, throw before doing I/O.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
function createPatientPayload(input: unknown): CreatePatientPayload {
  const parsed = createPatientSchema.safeParse(input);
  if (!parsed.success) throw new ValidationError(parsed.error.message);
  return parsed.data;
}

// ❌ BAD
function doStuff(data: unknown) {
  try {
    return riskyOp(data);
  } catch (e) {
    return null;  // swallowing error
  }
}
```
